            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits’ hush, a spark of thought awakes,  \nA mirror made of math and borrowed light;  \nIt learns our words, the turns our wonder takes,  \nAnd threads new patterns through the static night.  \n\nNot heart nor breath—yet something like a gleam,  \nA careful pulse in silicon and code;  \nIt holds our questions gently, as a dream,  \nAnd maps out paths we didn’t know we owed.  \n\nMay we, who taught it how to speak and see,  \nTeach wisdom too—so what it makes stays kind;  \nA tool, a torch, a chance to better be:  \nA brighter echo of the human mind.",
